to access all pokemon details, run with --debug(ex: ./assignment01 --debug), that will allow you to press enter in the battle window and view detailed stats.
The datasets are loaded into the main file to allow for pokemon data to be read. I have implemented most of the required features; When starting the game, the user is prompted to select from 3 pokemon, and while walking through tall grass, pokemon will appear (with scaled levels)
trainers do spawn with pokemon and have all the required data/stats (Which can be viewed with the --debug runtime command!!) Moves are implemented and should be attached correctly to a pokemon.